I'm a strawberry mute DIYer and have all these strawberry flavorings I had to give this one a shot, will report back in a few days to add rating and comments on whether it passes strawberry mute test:&#xD;
So after a 5 day steep it is incredible! I love how creamy cheeseshake this is as far as the strawberry goes I can pickup a bit on a syrupy sweet strawberry (my own doing via strawberry mute) not so much that it's like crystal clear authentic strawberry with syrup but it definitely adds an element of syrupy sweetness to that wonderfully creamy cheeseshake.&#xD;
&#xD;
2nd update: Circled back to this mix after about a month and oh boy is this deliciously creamy! Once finished with the remaining 20-30mls that was steeped for a month, I immediately went and mixed more to allow for an entire fully steeped batch. Excellent work!&#xD;
&#xD;
Great job! Thanks guys will mix again!

Excellent work guys. Well balanced. It has taken my ADV spot for now. Top 5 developed recipe, maybe even top 3.&#xD;
&#xD;
Description is accurate to what you get from this recipe. Top 3 developed recipe for me.&#xD;
Cheesecake element is present but light and it kinda blends into the ice cream. The graham crust is just present enough( I thought it would be substantially more with 3 tpa gc, and 2 inw ywcc.&#xD;
Strawberry is a light top note. Well balanced recipe, definitely worth the mix. 5 stars.
